  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Postoperative pain after cardiothoracic surgery can be a significant problem interfering with
      recovery, yet difficult to manage due to the sedating effects of opiates. These patients
      frequently have associated postoperative pulmonary changes and are at risk of respiratory
      depression with opioid analgesia. The ultrasound-guided transversus thoracic muscle plane
      block (TTMPB) is a recently described regional anesthetic technique showing improvements in
      postoperative pain management. Further investigation is needed to establish the potential of
      the TTMPB as an analgesic modality in congenital cardiothoracic surgery in patients under the
      age of 18.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
